title: Worship Practicum 1
description: Students will develop and practice skills in planning and leading Christian worship on a diverse student team. Activities include choosing and accompanying hymns, song-leading, teaching new music, the use of instrumental music, reading scripture, leading prayer, movement, and gesture.

title: Worship Practicum 2
description: A continuation of CMW201. Students will deepen skills in planning and leading Christian worship on a diverse student team. Activities include choosing and accompanying hymns, song-leading, teaching new music, the use of instrumental music, reading scripture, leading prayer, movement, and gesture. By the end of the term students will have planned and lead a church service as a team.
